6.31	Broseley	Broseley	Broseley is a small town in Shropshire, England with a population of 4,912 (2001 census). The River Severn flows to the north and east of the town. Broseley has a town council and is part of the area controlled by Shropshire Council. The first iron bridge in the world was built in 1779 to link Broseley with Coalbrookdale and Madeley. This led to the development of the Ironbridge Gorge, which is now part of a World Heritage Site.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Shropshire_UK_location_map.svg/240px-Shropshire_UK_location_map.svg.png
